  "title": "ISic003115. Funerary aedicola for Damatrios",
  "body": "<div id=\"editions\"><div class=\"attribution\">Text encoding: Jonathan Prag</div><div id=\"edition-interpretive\" lang=\"grc\">  <div class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\"><span class=\"ab\" id=\"div-interpretive\">  <a id=\"al1-interpretive\"><!--0--></a><span class=\"linenumber\">1</span><span data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"Δαμάτριος\n                    Ποπλείου\"><span data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Δαμάτριος\"><span data-text=\"Δαμάτριος\" data-n=\"5\" data-lemma=\"Δαμάτριος\">Δαμάτρι[ος]</span></span>  <br id=\"al2-interpretive\"><span class=\"linenumber\">2</span><span data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"Ποπλείου\"><span data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"patronym\" data-text=\"Ποπλείου\"><span data-text=\"Ποπλείου\" data-n=\"10\" data-lemma=\"Πόπλιος\">Ποπλείο[υ?]</span></span></span></span>  <br id=\"al3-interpretive\"><span class=\"linenumber\">3</span><span data-text=\"μακαρῖτα\" data-n=\"15\" data-lemma=\"μακαρίτης\">μακαρῖτα</span>  <br id=\"al4-interpretive\"><span class=\"linenumber\">4</span><span data-text=\"χαῖρηχαῖρε\" data-n=\"20\" data-lemma=\"χαίρω\">χαῖρη</span>  </span></div>  <p class=\"miniapp\">l.4 reg., orig. ΧΑΙΡΗχαῖρη</p></div><div class=\"attribution\">Text encoding: Dmitry Dundua, Robert Crellin</div><div id=\"edition-interpretive-simple-lemmatized\">  <div class=\"textpart\"><span class=\"ab\" id=\"div-interpretive\">  <span data-text=\"Δαμάτριος\" data-n=\"5\" data-lemma=\"Δαμάτριος\">Δαμάτριος</span>  <span data-text=\"Ποπλείου\" data-n=\"10\" data-lemma=\"Πόπλιος\">Ποπλείου</span>  <span data-text=\"μακαρῖτα\" data-n=\"15\" data-lemma=\"μακαρίτης\">μακαρῖτα</span>  <span data-text=\"χαῖρη\" data-n=\"20\" data-lemma=\"χαίρω\">χαῖρη</span>  </span></div>  <p class=\"miniapp\"></p></div><div class=\"attribution\">Text encoding: Jonathan Prag</div><div id=\"edition-diplomatic\" lang=\"grc\"><div class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\"><span class=\"ab\" id=\"div-diplomatic\"><a id=\"al1-diplomatic\"><!--0--></a><span class=\"linenumber\">1</span><span data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"Δαμάτριος\n                    Ποπλείου\"><span data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Δαμάτριος\"><span data-text=\"Δαμάτριος\" data-n=\"5\" data-lemma=\"Δαμάτριος\">ΔΑΜΑΤΡΙ[..]</span></span><br id=\"al2-diplomatic\"><span class=\"linenumber\">2</span><span data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"Ποπλείου\"><span data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"patronym\" data-text=\"Ποπλείου\"><span data-text=\"Ποπλείου\" data-n=\"10\" data-lemma=\"Πόπλιος\">ΠΟΠΛΕΙΟ[.]</span></span></span></span><br id=\"al3-diplomatic\"><span class=\"linenumber\">3</span><span data-text=\"μακαρῖτα\" data-n=\"15\" data-lemma=\"μακαρίτης\">ΜΑΚΑΡΙΤΑ</span><br id=\"al4-diplomatic\"><span class=\"linenumber\">4</span><span data-text=\"χαῖρηχαῖρε\" data-n=\"20\" data-lemma=\"χαίρω\">ΧΑΙΡΗ</span></span></div><p class=\"miniapp\">l.4 reg., orig. ΧΑΙΡΗχαῖρη</p></div><div class=\"attribution\">Text encoding: Dmitry Dundua, Robert Crellin</div><div id=\"edition-diplomatic-simple-lemmatized\"><div class=\"textpart\"><span class=\"ab\" id=\"div-diplomatic\"><span data-text=\"Δαμάτριος\" data-n=\"5\" data-lemma=\"Δαμάτριος\">ΔΑΜΑΤΡΙΟΣ</span><span data-text=\"Ποπλείου\" data-n=\"10\" data-lemma=\"Πόπλιος\">ΠΟΠΛΕΙΟΥ</span><span data-text=\"μακαρῖτα\" data-n=\"15\" data-lemma=\"μακαρίτης\">ΜΑΚΑΡΙΤΑ</span><span data-text=\"χαῖρη\" data-n=\"20\" data-lemma=\"χαίρω\">ΧΑΙΡΗ</span></span></div><p class=\"miniapp\"></p></div></div>  <div id=\"facsimile-images\"><h2>Facsimile Images</h2><a href=\"ISic003115_tiled.tif\"><img title=\"I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana; photo J. Prag 2023-07-18\" src=\"ISic003115_tiled-thumb.tif\"></a><a href=\"ISic003115.jpg\"><img title=\"I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana; photo J. Prag 2023-07-18\" src=\"ISic003115-thumb.jpg\"></a><a href=\"ISic003115_left_tiled.tif\"><img title=\"I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana; photo J. Prag 2023-07-18\" src=\"ISic003115_left_tiled-thumb.tif\"></a><a href=\"ISic003115_left.jpg\"><img title=\"I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana; photo J. Prag 2023-07-18\" src=\"ISic003115_left-thumb.jpg\"></a><a href=\"ISic003115_right_tiled.tif\"><img title=\"I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana; photo J. Prag 2023-07-18\" src=\"ISic003115_right_tiled-thumb.tif\"></a><a href=\"ISic003115_right.jpg\"><img title=\"I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana; photo J. Prag 2023-07-18\" src=\"ISic003115_right-thumb.jpg\"></a><a href=\"ISic003115_rear_tiled.tif\"><img title=\"I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana; photo J. Prag 2023-07-18\" src=\"ISic003115_rear_tiled-thumb.tif\"></a><a href=\"ISic003115_rear.jpg\"><img title=\"I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana; photo J. Prag 2023-07-18\" src=\"ISic003115_rear-thumb.jpg\"></a></div>  <div id=\"apparatus\"><h4>Apparatus criticus</h4><ul><li><span>  <span>Text of Brugnone2024, checked against photograph</span>  </span>; </li><li><span class=\"2\">2: <span>Brugnone: alternatively Ποπλείο[ς]</span>  </span></li></ul></div>  <div id=\"translation\"><h2> translation</h2><p class=\"translation-author\">  </p><p>Damatrios son of Popleios, blessed one, rejoice!</p>  </div>  <div id=\"commentary\"><h2>commentary</h2>  <p>The formula μακαρῖτα χαῖρε is found in another funerary epitaph at Lilybaeum, <a href=\"http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic003660\" target=\"_blank\">ISic003660</a>. The second name, Popleios (i.e. Latin Publius) could either be a patronymic, or else the adoption of a Latin name as a second name, as attested in other Sicilian cases (Cic. Verr. 2.4.35, 2.5.16).</p>  </div>  <div id=\"bibliography\"><h2>bibliography</h2>  <ul><li> 26.1075 <a href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000796\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000796</a>  </li><li> Manni Piraino 1976 213-215 no.1 tav.10.1 <a href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001771\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001771</a>  </li><li> Di Stefano 1984 178-179 no.193 fig.97 <a href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002035\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002035</a>  </li><li> Brugnone 2024 316-318 G8.5 fig.314 </li></ul>  <ul><li></li></ul>  </div>  <div id=\"handnote\"> Line 1-4  10-32  Interlineation line 1 to 2    </div><div id=\"license\"> Licensed under a Creative Commons-Attribution 4.0 licence. </div>",
